                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>By an exchange of notes, signed at La Paz, December 3 and 22, 1954, and entered
                    into force on the latter date (operative retroactively to September 4, 1953),
                    the United States and Bolivia agreed to extend and to amend the agreement of
                    September 4, 1941, as extended, providing for the services of a United States
                    military aviation mission in Bolivia; for text of the notes, see TIAS No. 3192,
                    or 6 UST 575.</p>
                <p>For text of the agreement of September 4, 1941, see 55 Stat. 1338.</p>
            </div>
